2 unit(s) Chicken Breasts
170 g Orzo
1 unit(s) Yellow Onion
28 g Baby Spinach
56 mL Cream
¼ cup Sun-Dried Tomato Pesto
¼ cup Parmesan Cheese, shredded
1 unit(s) Tomato
1 tbsp Zesty Garlic Blend
2 tbsp Unsalted Butter*
1 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Add 8 cups water and 1 tsp salt to a medium pot (use same for 4 ppl). Cover and bring to a boil over high heat.
Meanwhile, peel, then cut onion into 1/4-inch pieces.
If desired, roughly chop spinach.
Cut tomato into 1/2-inch pieces.

Add orzo to the boiling water. Cook uncovered, stirring occasionally, until tender, 10-12 min.
Reserve 1 cup (1 1/2 cups) orzo cooking water, then drain orzo and return to the same pot, off heat.
Add spinach and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter, then toss to coat until spinach wilts, 1 min. Cover to keep warm.

Meanwhile, pat chicken dry with paper towels. Cut into 1-inch pieces on a separate cutting board.
Combine salt, pepper and half the Zesty Garlic Blend in a medium bowl. Add chicken and toss to coat.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then chicken. Pan-fry, flipping occasionally, until cooked through, 4-5 min. **
Transfer chicken to a plate.

Reduce heat to medium, then add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter and onions to the same pan (from step 4). Season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring often, until tender, 4-5 min.
Add tomatoes and remaining Zesty Garlic Blend. Cook until tomatoes soften, 3-4 min.
Add cream, pesto, half the Parmesan and half the reserved pasta water. Bring to a simmer.
Add chicken and any juices from the plate. (TIP: For a lighter sauce, add more pasta water, 1-2 tbsp at a time.)

Divide orzo and spinach between bowls.
Top with 'Marry Me' chicken and sauce.
Sprinkle remaining Parmesan over top.

If you've opted to get chicken breasts, prep and cook them in the same way the recipe instructs you to cook the chicken tenders.